---
// The Challenge section for Energy industry page
---

<section id="challenge" class="cre-challenge-section">
  <div class="cre-challenge-container">
    <span class="section-label">THE CHALLENGE</span>
    <h2 class="cre-challenge-headline">
      Speed vs. accuracy in energy operations
    </h2>
    <p class="cre-challenge-subheadline">
      Energy operations move fast out of necessity. Grid demand shifts moment to moment. Equipment failures create cascade risk. Regulatory requirements tighten constantly. 
      But most energy companies are still running on legacy systems, manual processes, and disconnected data that can't keep up.
    </p>

    <!-- Highlight Box -->
    <div class="cre-highlight-box">
      <p class="cre-highlight-text">
        "The average energy operator loses 15-25% of potential revenue because they can't optimize asset performance and respond to operational changes fast enough."
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Challenge List -->
    <div class="cre-challenge-list-wrapper">
      <ul class="cre-challenge-list">
        <li><strong>Asset data is fragmented</strong> across SCADA systems, maintenance databases, and spreadsheets—making it impossible to get a unified view of asset health and predict failures before they happen.</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance scheduling is reactive</strong> instead of predictive, with crews responding to failures instead of preventing them, resulting in unplanned downtime and safety risks.</li>
        <li><strong>Operational performance tracking is delayed</strong>, requiring manual data aggregation from multiple sources, preventing real-time visibility into efficiency metrics and optimization opportunities.</li>
        <li><strong>Regulatory compliance is time-consuming</strong>, with manual tracking of requirements, manual report generation, and reactive response to audit findings instead of proactive management.</li>
        <li><strong>Energy trading and revenue optimization is manual</strong>, requiring analysts to manually assess market opportunities and asset availability instead of automating market participation.</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-functional coordination breaks down</strong> when operations, maintenance, and planning teams work in disconnected systems with different views of asset status and priorities.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Stat Cards -->
    <div class="cre-stat-cards">
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">15-25%</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">revenue lost</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">50+ hrs</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">monthly reporting</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">3-5 days</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">maintenance planning</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cre-challenge-section {
    background: #FFFFFF;
    padding: clamp(30px, 4vw, 50px) 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-headline {
    font-family: 'Figtree', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-subheadline {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-box {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border-left: 4px solid #0EA5E9;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-text {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #000000;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list-wrapper {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
    font-size: 17px; /* Increased from 16px for better readability */
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li::before {
    content: '−';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li strong {
    font-size: 17px; /* Match parent font size */
    color: #000000;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cre-stat-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-stat-card {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.2);
    padding: 32px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.4s ease;
  }

  .cre-stat-card:hover {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.4);
  }

  .cre-stat-number {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cre-stat-label {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .cre-challenge-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 16px; /* Slightly smaller on tablet */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 16px; /* Match tablet size */
    }

    .cre-stat-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cre-challenge-section {
      padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px) 24px;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 15px; /* Original size on mobile for space efficiency */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 15px; /* Match mobile size */
    }

    .cre-highlight-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .cre-stat-card {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>


